# ğŸ› ï¸ **Prerequisites**

Install these tools:

| Tool | Version | Link |
|------|---------|------|
| Docker Desktop | latest | https://www.docker.com/ |
| kubectl | latest | https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/ |
| Kind | latest | https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/ |
| Node.js | 18+ | https://nodejs.org/ |

Verify installation:

```powershell
docker --version
kubectl version --client
kind --version

ğŸ“¦ 1. Build Backend

Inside /backend:

docker build -t backend-app:latest .


Test locally (optional):

docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name backend-container backend-app:latest

ğŸ¨ 2. Build Frontend

Inside /frontend:

docker build -t frontend-app:latest .


Test locally (optional):

docker run -d -p 3000:80 --name frontend-container frontend-app:latest

ğŸš€ 3. Create Kind Cluster
kind create cluster --name fullstack-cluster


Verify:

kubectl get nodes

ğŸ“¥ 4. Load Docker Images Into Kind

Kind does NOT automatically use local Docker images.

kind load docker-image backend-app:latest --name fullstack-cluster
kind load docker-image frontend-app:latest --name fullstack-cluster

ğŸ“ 5. Apply Kubernetes Manifests

Deploy backend + frontend (in same pod):

kubectl apply -f k8s/


Check pods:

kubectl get pods


You should see:

fullstack-app-deployment-xxxxx   2/2     Running

ğŸŒ 6. Access the Application

Check the service:

kubectl get svc


Expected output:

3000:30080/TCP  # frontend â†’ http://localhost:30080
5000:30081/TCP  # backend  â†’ http://localhost:30081/api/users

âœ… Frontend

http://localhost:30080

âœ… Backend API

http://localhost:30081/api/users

ğŸ§¹ 7. Cleanup
kubectl delete -f k8s/
kind delete cluster --name fullstack-cluster
docker rm -f backend-container frontend-container
docker rmi backend-app:latest frontend-app:latest

ğŸ›‘ Common Issues & Fixes
Issue	Solution
ErrImageNeverPull	Run: kind load docker-image <image>
nodePort already allocated	Change NodePort in service.yaml
Frontend cannot reach backend	Use correct API URL â†’ http://localhost:30081
YAML errors	Ensure correct indentation and list syntax
Container name invalid	Names must be lowercase RFC1123
